                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote scope="major" script="naskh">
                        <desc><label>Script: </label>Small Naskh in black ink. Chapter headings in
                           white. Text is fully pointed. Recitation rules in red ink. Each juzʾ is
                           marked with a different flowerburst and foliate design. <label>Scribe:
                              </label><persName key="" role="scr">ʻAlī al-Naqshī</persName></desc>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>Folios 2b and 3a decorated in gold and other colours with floral and
                        foliate designs in blue, green, gold, red, and pink. Verse endings are
                        marked with gold roundels. Text boxes are in gold with red
                        outlines.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <p>Eastern binding in reddish-brown leather over boards with gold borders and a
                        central floral spray. Doublures have blue pastedowns. Envelope flap.</p>
                  </bindingDesc>
